caption: According to the texts on the statue,  In memory of the fallen soldiers of the Russian expeditionary corps  fighting on the french fields between 1916-1918. Grateful France and Russia
The monument that was missing in France in recognition of the military exploits of the 20,000 soldiers and officers of the Russian Expeditionary Force in France during the Great War.
Work created by the Russian artist Vladimir Sourovtsev.  Built in Paris, Place du Canada (8th).
